The secret of splendor over Norway solved: the Russians tested a missile
A special luminous effect of unknown origin was observed in Norway.
The Russian Defense Ministry acknowledged yesterday that near the borders with Norway it tested an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The missile, of the type "Bulava", formerly intended to be the pride of the Russian army, is becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Even its repeated presence in the missile tests has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Bulavá, in most cases, did not fly out or there was a failure in the air.
In Russian newspapers they write of "Bulava" as "a missile that does not fly".
A missile that does not fly, but shines.
During this, the 13th test, there was no problem at first.
At the end of the flight there were again technical problems in the aircraft.
Probably the engine exploded in the third stage of the missile.
This time "Bulava" was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskoy, which floated submerged in the White Sea.
This type of missile makes it possible to launch from a vessel that is moving and is submerged at the same time.
That is why it is likely that the mysterious light over Norway, caused by an unidentified flying object, was actually the failed "Bulavá".
The Norwegians did not hesitate from the first moment that it was a Russian missile.
The generals this time defend themselves by stating that one cannot speak simply of a failure.
The first two stages of the missile endured and the failure occurred in the third.
In the previous cases, the engines were immediately damaged in the first stage.
Although none of the launches went completely error-free, according to the Ministry of Defense management, only six of the thirteen failed.
The success of almost fifty percent is full of optimism to the generals and that is why they continue to say that "Bulavá" will one day fly smoothly and that it will even manage to carry up to ten nuclear hypersonic blocks, whose total maximum weight is 1.15 tons.
