Service providers and solutions for accident assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information provided by the manufacturers, then elaborating it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the evaluations are made with its products.
The other companies competing in the field of assessment and information processing tools are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been released than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, these companies get to work.
It is a very difficult job, because you have to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and enter its price.
In addition, from each model is made a "smart" graphic image where you can "pinch" different parts of tourism.
If it’s a massive sales model, the job can be ready in a week if the process goes very fast.
If it is a minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile park that circulates, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documentation and the development of the databases, Audatex has eight centers spread around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
